"The basic impact of the revolution comes from the hardware - every type of office machinery is being replaced by equipment that didn't exist 20 or even ten years ago. But the powers of the programs and networks are also prodigious. The author describes the extraordinary uses to which the new technology is already being put - and the necessary changes in management style and structuring which result. Robert Heller has also written \"The New Naked Manager\", \"The Pocket Manager\", \"The Supermanagers\", \"The Age of the Common Millionaire\" and \"The Decision Makers\"."
